  "page_number": 3,
  "context": "III. Terms Defined\n\nCompensatory Overtime Credits (COCs) – are any units of WL aside from actual teaching load in excess of 24 units/ term. These are pooled/lumped into compensatory time-offs (CTOS) by the HRMO that can be used by any faculty to cover his/her absences or undertime.\n\nSeasonal/Occasional Designations – refer to designations which do not require daily and weekly client engagement, and monthly submissions of reportorial requirements and conduct of office-initiated activities.\n\nTeaching Load (TL) refers to actual teaching loads given to faculty members measured in hours load of subjects to teach (under a. instruction) assigned to a teacher. It excludes work assignments in b) research, c) extension, d) production and e) others/administrative designations.\n\nIllustration:\n\n| Credit Unit(s) | Teaching Hour(s) | Teaching Load (in hours) |\n|---|---|---|\n| 3 (Lec) | 3 | 3 |\n| 2 (Lec) | 2 | 2 |\n| 1 (Lec) | 1 | 1 |\n\n| Credit Unit(s) | Teaching Hour(s) | Teaching Load (in hours), except high- risk laboratory work exposure(s) |\n|---|---|---|\n| 3 (Lab) | 9 | 6.25 |\n| 2 (Lab) | 6 | 4.5 |\n| 1 (Lab) | 3 | 2.25 |",
  "qa_pairs": [
    {
      "question": "What are Compensatory Overtime Credits (COCs)?",
      "answer": "Compensatory Overtime Credits (COCs) refer to any units of Workload aside from actual teaching load in excess of 24 units per term. These are pooled/lumped into compensatory time-offs (CTOS) by the HRMO that can be used by any faculty member to cover absences or undertime."
